      "text": "©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY\n\nThinh Nguyen Senior Manager, Interconnection Projects\n\nInterconnection Order No. 2023 Proposed Compliance Approach\n\nInterconnection Issues Task Force (IITF) November 2, 2023\n\nAgenda \n Regulatory Updates (FERC and NYSERDA) \n Proposed Study Deposits \n Proposed Commercial Readiness Deposits \n Proposed Withdrawal Fees \n Transitional Cluster Fees \n Proposed Prioritization \n Next Steps \n\nFERC Order Extending \nOrder No. 2023 \nCompliance Filing \nDeadline \n\nFERC Order Extending Order No. 2023 Compliance \nFiling Deadline \n On October 25, 2023, FERC issued an order that, among other things, extends the \nOrder No. 2023 Compliance Filing Deadline to April 3, 2024. \n The date of the NYISO’s compliance filing and start date for the rolling Pre \nApplication Process is yet to be determined. \n\nTransition Process Timeline *For the purpose of this timeline, on October 25, 2023, FERC extended the Compliance Filing Deadline to April 3, 2024. The date of the NYISO’s compliance filing and start date for the rolling Pre Application Process is yet to be determined.\n\nNYSERDA RESRFI23-1 ©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY 7\n\nNYSERDA Request for Information \n(RESRFI23-1) \n On October 26, 2023, NYSERDA issued a Request for Information \n(RFI) seeking information from stakeholders on the potential \nstructure and merits of an expedited solicitation for Renewable \nEnergy Standard Tier 1 Certificates (RECs) \n NYISO has updated its proposed Transition Process Timeline (see \nslides 5 and 35) to reflect the recent changes in the regulatory \nlandscape at FERC. \n\nProposed Study Deposits ©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY 9\n\nStudy Deposits/Fees  Non-refundable Application Fee submitted with Interconnection Request during the Application Window: $10,000  One Time Study Deposit based on size of project submitted with Interconnection Request:\n\n If Small Generating Facilities are included in Cluster Study Process, the one-time study deposit for these \nfacilities is $100,000. \n For CRIS only projects, the one-time study deposit is $50,000. \n\nSize of Proposed Generating Facility Associated with Interconnection Request\n\nAmount of Deposit\n\n< 80 MW $100,000 \n≥ 80 MW < 200 MW $150,000 \n≥ 200 MW $250,000 \n\nStudy Deposits/Fees cont’d. \n The NYISO will invoice Developers actual study costs on a monthly \nbasis and will only draw on the Study Deposit if a Developer fails to \npay its monthly invoice. \n Study Deposit will remain in place for duration of the Cluster Study \nProcess and will be subject to withdrawal penalties as described \nbelow. \n If, at the completion of Phase 2 of the Cluster Study Process, \nDeveloper accepts its cost allocation and posts security, the NYISO \nwill refund the Study Deposit amount in full. \n\nProposed Commercial Readiness Deposits\n\nCommercial Readiness Deposits\n\n$4,000/MW\n\nTo enter Phase 1 (Phase 1 Deposit)\n\nTo enter Phase 2 (Phase 2 Deposit)\n\n• NYISO will not require demonstration of a Regulatory Milestone. • Deposits are cumulative, not additive. • If Small Generating Facilities are included in Cluster Study Process, they will have to satisfy these requirements.\n\nThe greater of (i) Phase 1 Deposit, and (ii) 20% of cost estimate determined in Phase 1 (cost estimates include: Local SUF and CTOAF)\n\n| At conclusion of Phase 2 in | 100% of costs estimate of |\n| --- | --- |\n| Decision Period (pay cash | SUFs, SDUs, and CTOAFs |\n| and/or security) | identified in Phase 1 and |\n\nPhase 2 ©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY © COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED. DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY 13\n\nWithdrawal Penalties ©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY 14\n\nWithdrawal Penalties \n If a project withdrawals during Customer Engagement Window or at the Decision \nPoint to Enter Phase 1, it forfeits 25% of its Study Deposit. \n If a project withdraws at or before the Decision Point at the conclusion of Phase 1, \nit forfeits 50% of the Study Deposit and 10% of the Phase 1 Deposit. \n If a project withdraws at or before the Decision Point at the conclusion of Phase 2, \nit forfeits 100% of the Study Deposit and 20% of the Phase 2 Deposit. \n If a project accepts its project cost allocation and pays cash or posts Security, and \nlater withdraws, it may forfeit up to 100% of this deposit if other projects are relying \non the upgraded facilities. \n Any withdrawal penalties will first be used to offset the study costs of the remaining \nprojects in the cluster that have accepted their cost allocation and posted security. \n If penalty costs have been collected greater than actual study costs amounts for a \ngiven cluster, this amount will be used to offset Rate Schedule 1 costs \n\nTransition Cluster Fees/Deposits\n\nTransition Cluster Fees/Deposits  All Developers electing to participate in the Transition Cluster Study must submit $10,000 non-refundable application fee with IR submittal during the Application Window along with the applicable Study Deposits.  NYISO will not require the $5M transition fee, as described in Order No. 2023.\n\nProposed Prioritization ©COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY 18\n\nPrioritization for Feasibility Issues \n As a general matter, projects participating in a Cluster Study \nwill not have priority over other projects participating in the \nsame study based on queue number. \n Priority rules will only be triggered in the event of certain \nphysical infeasibility determinations that result in a “jump ball” \nbetween two similarly situated projects for access to limited \npoints of interconnection. \n NYISO will provide additional details concerning the priority \nrules in its next presentation. \n\n© COPYRIGHT NYISO 2023. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED. DRAFT – FOR DISCUSSION PURPOSES ONLY\n\nNext Steps\n\nNext Steps \n Compliance proposals to be discussed in increasing detail \nat Interconnection Task Force meetings. Upcoming IITF meetings: \n• November 14 \n• December 1 \n• December 14 \n• January 11 \n\nAppendix A: NYISO’s Proposed Cluster Study Overview\n\nProposed Cluster Study Overview\n\nProposed Cluster Study Process \nNYISO Compliance Approach \n Key Aspects: \n• An overall timeline that aligns with the timeline laid out in Order No. \n2023. \n• A rolling, optional pre-application process; \n• An enhanced scope for the Customer Engagement Window (including a \nphysical infeasibility screen); \n• A two-phase Cluster Study that incorporates SRIS-type analyses and \nClass Year analyses (including POI upgrades) rather than an SRIS-type \ncluster followed by an individual facilities study; \n• Limited project modifications (to be discussed further in future \nmeetings) and opportunities to cure deficiencies \n\nProposed Cluster Study Process \nNYISO Compliance Approach \n Key Aspects, cont.: \n• Inability for projects to move forward if deemed physically infeasible (to be \ndiscussed further in future meetings) \n• Increased financial commitments, including deposits aligned with those in \nOrder No. 2023 (to be discussed further in future meetings); \n• More stringent Site Control requirements (to be discussed further in future \nmeetings) \n• Key aspect for consideration: Incorporating Small Generating Facilities into \nthe Cluster Study Process \n Additional aspects and details under development to be discussed in future \nmeetings \n\nProposed Cluster Study Structure and Timeline\n\nNYISO’s Proposed Cluster Study Process,\n\ncont.\n\nTotal Timeline: 569 days (1.6 years) Total Timeline in Order No. 2023: 495 days to 585 days (1.4 – 1.6 years) (see Appendix for details re: Order No. 2023 Cluster Study structure and timeline)\n\nStudy Complete\n\nIterative Decision Period\n\n7-day decision period (1 Round)\n\n7-day decision period (1 Round)\n\nCluster Study Phase 1 (Local SUF) (180 days)\n\nCluster Study Phase 2 \n(Clus",
